main event: A woman in Brandon, Florida observed an unidentified copper-colored object in the sky in December 1966.
interesting points: The object looked like a hat with a flat top, and was above the size of a two-engine aircraft.
The object came out from behind a cloud, remained stationary for about a minute, and then went back into the same cloud.
The object did not reappear from the cloud.
The witness had training in aircraft recognition and worked as a defense worker in Cleveland, Ohio.
The investigator believed the witness was telling the truth about the sighting, but the investigation was hampered by the witness's inability to recall the exact date and time.
witnesses: Mrs. J., a civilian with aircraft recognition training
photographs: Yes, but not included in the report
